{{Top|leg}}
An '''electrorangefinder''' was a device that calculated the distance between itself and a target object. These devices were incorporated into [[Electrobinoculars/Legends|electrobinoculars]] and [[Macrobinoculars/Legends|macrobinoculars]] and were essential components in the targeting and fire-control computers used by artillery and ship-mounted weapons systems.

